@markusweimer @tcNickolas Resolved the conflicts. Please try this again.

@tcNickolas did you do a deep clean prior to running your tests last time? This PR also involves Java changes so you may need to delete the `bin` folder before rebuilding the .NET codebase such that it exhibits behavior that reflects the changes in Java.

Thanks!

@tcNickolas I had an overall look. One comment: There are additional useful logs in BroadcastReduce examples that you can test for. Specifically, in Org.Apache.REEF.IMRU.Examples.PipelinedBroadcastReduce.BroadcastSenderReduceReceiverUpdateFunction
we print the value received in each iteration. Might be worthwhile to check that.

Similarly in Org.Apache.REEF.IMRU.Examples.MapperCount.MapperCountUpdateFunction, the input in Update function there is basically total mapper count. We can introduce a log in that function and then check the value.
